ciscoTsIpAddr.name: ciscoTsIpAddr
ciscoTsIpAddr.description: The IP address of the current Token Ring Bridge Relay Facility (TrBRF).

ciscoTsNetMask.name: ciscoTsNetMask
ciscoTsNetMask.description: The subnet mask of the current TrBRF.

ciscoTsDefaultGateway.name: ciscoTsDefaultGateway
ciscoTsDefaultGateway.description: IP default gateway of the current TrBRF.

ciscoTsSysCurTime.name: ciscoTsSysCurTime
ciscoTsSysCurTime.description: Current time at the switch. To set the time use the format yyyy mm dd hh mm ss. All fields are required. Setting this object will reset the time in all the switches in the stack to the new value.

ciscoTsConfiguration.name: ciscoTsConfiguration
ciscoTsConfiguration.description: The stack configuration of the system. A system can exist in three possible configurations. 1. Stand alone mode where the system has only one switch and is not connected to any other switches. 2. Back to Back mode in which a pair of switches are connected back to back through Stack Port. 3. Matrix mode in which the stack has up to eight switches connected to a Matrix through the Stack Port.

ciscoTsNumSwitches.name: ciscoTsNumSwitches
ciscoTsNumSwitches.description: Total number of switches in the stack.

ciscoTsStackStatus.name: ciscoTsStackStatus
ciscoTsStackStatus.description: Stack status indicates if the stack is going through the Stack Management Update protocol. Management stations should check this status if they receive a genErr on a SET request for any of the stack wide attributes.

ciscoTsTftpServerTrBRF.name: ciscoTsTftpServerTrBRF
ciscoTsTftpServerTrBRF.description: TrBRF to which the server is connected.

ciscoTsTftpFileLoc.name: ciscoTsTftpFileLoc
ciscoTsTftpFileLoc.description: Path and filename of the binary file on the server.

ciscoTsTftpDownload.name: ciscoTsTftpDownload
ciscoTsTftpDownload.description: Setting this to any number between 1 and 8 starts a TFTP download for that box. Setting this to 9 starts a TFTP download for all boxes in a stack. This object will always return a zero on a get request. If RMON is enabled on the switch or stack, then setting this object will cause the RMON feature to be disabled until the switch or stack is rebooted.

ciscoTsTftpDownloadStatus.name: ciscoTsTftpDownloadStatus
ciscoTsTftpDownloadStatus.description: Reading complete(2) from this object means the write to flash has succeeded and the switch is ready to be rebooted.

ciscoTsProStackMatrixStatus.name: ciscoTsProStackMatrixStatus
ciscoTsProStackMatrixStatus.description: Status of the Active Matrix module in the stack. This object is set to none(3) if the switch is not connected to a Matrix.

ciscoTsNumMatrixModules.name: ciscoTsNumMatrixModules
ciscoTsNumMatrixModules.description: Number of Matrix modules in the stack. This object is set to zero if the switch is not connected to a Matrix.

ciscoTsStackReset.name: ciscoTsStackReset
ciscoTsStackReset.description: Operational status of the controlling switch in the stack. Setting this value to either coldReset(2) or warmReset(3) will cause all boxes in the stack to cold start or warm start after a predefined time delay.

ciscoTsStackRMONStatistics.name: ciscoTsStackRMONStatistics
ciscoTsStackRMONStatistics.description: Used to enable or disable the collection of RMON statistics on the switch/stack. After changing the state of this object, the switch must be rebooted for the changes to take effect.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrTable.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrTable
ciscoTsTrapRcvrTable.description: Trap Receiver Table for each TrBRF.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrEntry.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrEntry
ciscoTsTrapRcvrEntry.description: Definition of each row in the TrBRF specific trap receiver table.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrIndex.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrIndex
ciscoTsTrapRcvrIndex.description: Trap receiver index for each entry. The switch only allows 20 entries into this table.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrStatus.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrStatus
ciscoTsTrapRcvrStatus.description: Setting the value of this object to invalid(3) deletes the row from the table. The value invalid(3) should never be returned on a GET. Setting this value to create(4) causes a new row to be created if the row does not already exist. To create a new row set ciscoTsTrapRcvrStatus to create(4) and ciscoTsTrapRcvrIndex to any valid index which does not already exist. The value returned on GETs should be valid(2) or other(1), which is used to indicate any other condition.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrIpAddress.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrIpAddress
ciscoTsTrapRcvrIpAddress.description: IP address for an SNMP manager that is to receive the trap.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrComm.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrComm
ciscoTsTrapRcvrComm.description: Community string to use in outgoing traps.

ciscoTsTrapRcvrTrBRFs.name: ciscoTsTrapRcvrTrBRFs
ciscoTsTrapRcvrTrBRFs.description: TrBRFs on which traps to this target are sent. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight TrBRFs, with the first octet specifying TrBRFs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying TrBRFs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered TrBRF, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered TrBRF. Thus, each TrBRF of the stack is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that TrBRF is included in the set of TrBRFs sending traps; the TrBRF is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. The default is all zeros. Reading all of the entries in the ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTable will give the possible valid bits that can be set. A value of all FF's will enable traps on all configured TrBRFs.

ciscoTsStackTable.name: ciscoTsStackTable
ciscoTsStackTable.description: Stack information table. This table provides the current configuration of the stack. It also provides a mapping of Switch Numbers to their addresses. There is one entry in this table for each switch in the stack. Entries cannot be administratively created/deleted. The Management Application is required to retrieve this table and verify its own view of the stack periodically and/or when it receives a trap indicating a change in the stack configuration.

ciscoTsStackEntry.name: ciscoTsStackEntry
ciscoTsStackEntry.description: Definition of each row in the Stack Table

ciscoTsStackSwitchNumber.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchNumber
ciscoTsStackSwitchNumber.description: Switch number as determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoTsStackSwitchBIAddr.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchBIAddr
ciscoTsStackSwitchBIAddr.description: The burned in MAC address of the switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchLAAddr.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchLAAddr
ciscoTsStackSwitchLAAddr.description: The locally administered MAC address of the switch. After writing to this object, you must reset the switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchFwVersion.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchFwVersion
ciscoTsStackSwitchFwVersion.description: Version number for the firmware running on the switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchHwVersion.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchHwVersion
ciscoTsStackSwitchHwVersion.description: Hardware version number for the switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchUptime.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchUptime
ciscoTsStackSwitchUptime.description: Time ticks since the switch was last reset.

ciscoTsStackSwitchStatus.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchStatus
ciscoTsStackSwitchStatus.description: Operational status of the box. Setting this value to either coldReset(2) or warmReset(3) will cause cold start or warm start to occur after a predefined time delay.

ciscoTsStackSwitchTemperature.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchTemperature
ciscoTsStackSwitchTemperature.description: Temperature of each switch reported in degrees Celsius.

ciscoTsStackSwitchMemory.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchMemory
ciscoTsStackSwitchMemory.description: Installed memory on the switch in MB.

ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANPort.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANPort
ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANPort.description: Port number to be used for the Switch Port Analyzer. Setting this object to zero turns off the SPAN function.

ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredPort.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredPort
ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredPort.description: Port monitored by the SPAN function.

ciscoTsStackSwitchFeatureStatus.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchFeatureStatus
ciscoTsStackSwitchFeatureStatus.description: This object indicates whether the switch is enabled to support enhanced features.

ciscoTsStackSwitchFeatureKey.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchFeatureKey
ciscoTsStackSwitchFeatureKey.description: Feature key to enable enhanced features. See the manual for information pertaining to enabling possible enhanced features.

ciscoTsStackSwitchPorts.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchPorts
ciscoTsStackSwitchPorts.description: A bit mask representing all the ports present in this switch. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports in this switch; the port is not included in this switch if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoTsStackSwitchAgingTime.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchAgingTime
ciscoTsStackSwitchAgingTime.description: Aging time in minutes for the master address table entries on this switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchAgingLevel.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchAgingLevel
ciscoTsStackSwitchAgingLevel.description: Threshold to demand age the master address table. All numbers refer to percentage of the address table. The only values accepted by the agent are 50,60,70,80,90 and 0. Setting the value to 0 disables demand aging.

ciscoTsStackSwitchRcvdFrames.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchRcvdFrames
ciscoTsStackSwitchRcvdFrames.description: Frames received for processing by the CPU.

ciscoTsStackSwitchRcvdErrFrames.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchRcvdErrFrames
ciscoTsStackSwitchRcvdErrFrames.description: Error frames received by the CPU.

ciscoTsStackSwitchLostFrames.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchLostFrames
ciscoTsStackSwitchLostFrames.description: Frames lost by the CPU while trying to transmit.

ciscoTsStackSwitchPendingSendRqsts.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchPendingSendRqsts
ciscoTsStackSwitchPendingSendRqsts.description: Frames queued in the CPU's transmit buffer.

ciscoTsStackSwitchXmitErrFrames.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchXmitErrFrames
ciscoTsStackSwitchXmitErrFrames.description: Frames in error due to buffer overflows or drops in the CPU.

ciscoTsStackSwitchCurrActStations.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchCurrActStations
ciscoTsStackSwitchCurrActStations.description: The number of station address entries currently active in the switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchLargestNumStations.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchLargestNumStations
ciscoTsStackSwitchLargestNumStations.description: The largest number of active stations ever seen on the switch since the last reboot, or clearing of statistics.

ciscoTsStackSwitchMaxAddressChain.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchMaxAddressChain
ciscoTsStackSwitchMaxAddressChain.description: The longest chain of addresses anywhere in the CPU's address hash table.

ciscoTsStackSwitchAddressTblFulls.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchAddressTblFulls
ciscoTsStackSwitchAddressTblFulls.description: The number of times a hash table chain has filled up.

ciscoTsStackSwitchId.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchId
ciscoTsStackSwitchId.description: The object ID used to uniquely identify the type of Cisco token ring switch.

ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredTrCRFs.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredTrCRFs
ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredTrCRFs.description: Token Ring Concentrator Facilities (TrCRFs) for which traffic on the port specified by ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredPort should be monitored. Individual TrCRFs can be selected for monitoring only on trunk ports. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight TrCRFs, with the first octet specifying TrCRFs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying TrCRFs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered TrCRF, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered TrCRF. Thus, each TrCRF of the stack is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that TrCRF is included in the set of TrCRFs for which traffic should be monitored ; the TrCRF is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. The default is all zeros. Get requests for this object will return all zeros if ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredPort specifies a non-trunk port. Set requests for this object will be rejected with a 'badValue' error if ciscoTsStackSwitchSPANMonitoredPort specifies a non-trunk port.

ciscoTsStackSwitchPwrSupplyStatus.name: ciscoTsStackSwitchPwrSupplyStatus
ciscoTsStackSwitchPwrSupplyStatus.description: The status of the power supply of the switch. The values have the following meanings: unknown(1) : The status is not known. internal-only(2) : The switch is not capable of redundant power. internal-no-backup(3) : The switch is capable of redundant power, but is currently operating on the internal supply with no RPS attached. internal-backup-will-reset(4) : The switch is capable of redundant power and is currently opertaing on the internal supply. A RPS is attached, but if the internal supply fails there will be a reset. external-no-backup(5) : The switch is capable of redundant power and is currently operating on a single external RPS connection. external-backup-no-reset(6) : The switch is capable of redundant power and is currently operating with a y-connected external RPS. If one supply in the RPS fails there will be no interuption of operation.

ciscoTsModTable.name: ciscoTsModTable
ciscoTsModTable.description: Module configuration table. There is one entry in the table for each module in a stack. Entries cannot be administratively created/deleted.

ciscoTsModEntry.name: ciscoTsModEntry
ciscoTsModEntry.description: Definition of each row in the Module Table

ciscoTsModSwitchNumber.name: ciscoTsModSwitchNumber
ciscoTsModSwitchNumber.description: Switch number as determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoTsModState.name: ciscoTsModState
ciscoTsModState.description: The state indicates the current operational state of the module.

ciscoTsModType.name: ciscoTsModType
ciscoTsModType.description: The type of module plugged in to the slot. Module type system(1) represents the mother board with the CPU and system memory. Module state none(10) represents a slot with no modules plugged in (indicated by ciscoTsModState).

ciscoTsModNumPorts.name: ciscoTsModNumPorts
ciscoTsModNumPorts.description: Total number of ports in the module.

ciscoTsModUptime.name: ciscoTsModUptime
ciscoTsModUptime.description: Time ticks since the module was last reset.

ciscoTsPortCfgTable.name: ciscoTsPortCfgTable
ciscoTsPortCfgTable.description: A table of configuration information about each port. There is one entry for each port in a stack. Entries cannot be administratively created/deleted.

ciscoTsPortCfgEntry.name: ciscoTsPortCfgEntry
ciscoTsPortCfgEntry.description: Definition of rows in the port configuration table.

ciscoTsPortCfgNumber.name: ciscoTsPortCfgNumber
ciscoTsPortCfgNumber.description: A unique value for each port entry. The value corresponds the port number.

ciscoTsPortCfgModNumber.name: ciscoTsPortCfgModNumber
ciscoTsPortCfgModNumber.description: Module number of the module that contains this port.

ciscoTsPortCfgIfIndex.name: ciscoTsPortCfgIfIndex
ciscoTsPortCfgIfIndex.description: A pointer to the entry in the ifTable corresponding to this port.

ciscoTsPortCfgResetStats.name: ciscoTsPortCfgResetStats
ciscoTsPortCfgResetStats.description: Setting this object to reset(3) causes all traffic counters for this port to be set to zero. Also the value of ciscoTsPortStatsResetTimer is set to zero.

ciscoTsPortCfgResetAddrs.name: ciscoTsPortCfgResetAddrs
ciscoTsPortCfgResetAddrs.description: Setting this object to reset(3) clears all address table entries for this port as well as setting all port traffic counters to zero and setting ciscoTsPortStatsResetTimer to zero.

ciscoTsPortCfgAddrAgingTime.name: ciscoTsPortCfgAddrAgingTime
ciscoTsPortCfgAddrAgingTime.description: Port level address aging time in minutes. Setting this object to zero disables address aging.

ciscoTsPortCfgDemandAgingLevel.name: ciscoTsPortCfgDemandAgingLevel
ciscoTsPortCfgDemandAgingLevel.description: Threshold to demand age the port address table. All numbers refer to percentage of the address table. The only values accepted by the agent are 50,60,70,80,90 and 0. Setting the value to 0 disables demand aging.

ciscoTsPortCfgErrLoThreshold.name: ciscoTsPortCfgErrLoThreshold
ciscoTsPortCfgErrLoThreshold.description: Lower error rate threshold which causes the port to transition from store and forward mode to cut-through mode.

ciscoTsPortCfgErrHiThreshold.name: ciscoTsPortCfgErrHiThreshold
ciscoTsPortCfgErrHiThreshold.description: Upper error rate threshold which causes the port to transition from cut-through mode to store and forward mode.

ciscoTsPortCfgMaxTransmitUnit.name: ciscoTsPortCfgMaxTransmitUnit
ciscoTsPortCfgMaxTransmitUnit.description: MTU size. The valid values for this object are 1500, 4472, 8144 and 17800. The value specified cannot exceed the vtpVlanMTU (see Cisco VTP MIB) for the TrBRF that this port is a member of. Set requests for invalid values will be rejected with a 'badValue' error.

ciscoTsPortCfgMaxExplorerRate.name: ciscoTsPortCfgMaxExplorerRate
ciscoTsPortCfgMaxExplorerRate.description: Explorer frame forwarding rate per second throttle. A value of (-1) disables explorer frame throttling.

ciscoTsPortCfgSetACbits.name: ciscoTsPortCfgSetACbits
ciscoTsPortCfgSetACbits.description: Specifies if the AC bits shall be set unconditionally when a port forwards certain LLC frames.

ciscoTsPortCfgForwardingMode.name: ciscoTsPortCfgForwardingMode
ciscoTsPortCfgForwardingMode.description: Operational frame switching mode for the port. When in auto mode the port uses the Direct Cut algorithm to place the port in either cutthru(3) or storeandforward(2) mode.

ciscoTsPortCfgActualForwardingMode.name: ciscoTsPortCfgActualForwardingMode
ciscoTsPortCfgActualForwardingMode.description: Actual operational frame switching mode for the port.

ciscoTsPortCfgPortMode.name: ciscoTsPortCfgPortMode
ciscoTsPortCfgPortMode.description: Port operation mode. Only the HDX and FDX modes can be auto detected. Note, that passive-probe(7) mode can not be set with this object. The passive-probe(7) mode is set automatically when a passive probe is defined in the ciscoTsPassiveProbeTable. Note also that ri-ro(6) is only valid for ports 19, 20 (Catalyst 3900), and ports on a fiber module.

ciscoTsPortCfgActualPortMode.name: ciscoTsPortCfgActualPortMode
ciscoTsPortCfgActualPortMode.description: The actual port operation mode. If the port is in auto mode, this object will return the mode that the port opened in.

ciscoTsPortCfgPriorityThres.name: ciscoTsPortCfgPriorityThres
ciscoTsPortCfgPriorityThres.description: The highest token-ring frame priority that shall go to the low-priority transmit queue.

ciscoTsPortCfgMinXmitPriority.name: ciscoTsPortCfgMinXmitPriority
ciscoTsPortCfgMinXmitPriority.description: The minimum token priority that will be used for transmit.

ciscoTsPortCfgCfgLossThres.name: ciscoTsPortCfgCfgLossThres
ciscoTsPortCfgCfgLossThres.description: Number of configuration loss events (described in TsPortCfgLossRC) during the sample period which, if exceeded, should cause the port to be disabled. If the port is disabled by this function the port must be manually re-enabled.

ciscoTsPortCfgCfgLossInterval.name: ciscoTsPortCfgCfgLossInterval
ciscoTsPortCfgCfgLossInterval.description: The sampling period, in minutes, for which the port monitors to determine if the configuration loss threshold has been exceeded.

ciscoTsPortCfgBcastSuppresion.name: ciscoTsPortCfgBcastSuppresion
ciscoTsPortCfgBcastSuppresion.description: The number of broadcast frames per second allowed to be forwarded by this port. Any broadcast frames exceeding this watermark will not be forwarded by the port. Setting this object to 0 turns broadcast suppression off.

ciscoTsPortCfgCDPTimeToLive.name: ciscoTsPortCfgCDPTimeToLive
ciscoTsPortCfgCDPTimeToLive.description: The advertised time-to-live parameter on all CDP messages generated by this switch on this port.

ciscoTsPortCfgSpanningTreeMode.name: ciscoTsPortCfgSpanningTreeMode
ciscoTsPortCfgSpanningTreeMode.description: Used when configuring manual spanning tree. Setting this object to forwarding(2) or blocking(3) overrides the TrCRF's spanning tree's algorithm for this port.

ciscoTsPortCfgSecurityMode.name: ciscoTsPortCfgSecurityMode
ciscoTsPortCfgSecurityMode.description: Port security mode is used to disable address learning at a port where an allow-source or allow-destination MAC address filter is configured. A value of normal(1) indicates that the port is not configured for security. A value of secure-src-addrs(2) indicates that learning for source addresses is disabled. A value of secure-dest-addrs(3) indicates that learning for destination addresses is disabled. A value of secure-src-and-dest-addrs(4) indicates that learning is disabled for both source and destination addresses.

ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrThreshold.name: ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrThreshold
ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrThreshold.description: The number of soft errors reported from a station connected to this port which, if exceeded, should cause a soft error exceeded trap to be issued. The error counters being monitored and compared to this threshold value are all of the error counters in the ringStationTable (see RFC 1513).

ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrReportInterval.name: ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrReportInterval
ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrReportInterval.description: The sampling period, in seconds, in which each station connected to this port will be monitored for excessive soft error reports. If a station reports more than ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrThreshold errors within the sampling period a trap will be issued to the management station(s). Setting a value of 0 will cause no traps to be sent for this port.

ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrorMonitoring.name: ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrorMonitoring
ciscoTsPortCfgSoftErrorMonitoring.description: Used to enable or disable, for this port, the collection of soft error statistics and the sending of traps when the configured error threshold is exceeded. If RMON statistics collection is not enabled, then the soft error statistics will only be available from the console.

ciscoTsPortStatsTable.name: ciscoTsPortStatsTable
ciscoTsPortStatsTable.description: A table of statistical information about each port. There is one entry for each port in a stack. Entries cannot be administratively created/deleted

ciscoTsPortStatsEntry.name: ciscoTsPortStatsEntry
ciscoTsPortStatsEntry.description: Definition of rows in the port statistics table.

ciscoTsPortStatsNumber.name: ciscoTsPortStatsNumber
ciscoTsPortStatsNumber.description: A unique value for each port entry. The value corresponds the port number.

ciscoTsPortStatsModNumber.name: ciscoTsPortStatsModNumber
ciscoTsPortStatsModNumber.description: Module number of the module that contains this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsIfIndex.name: ciscoTsPortStatsIfIndex
ciscoTsPortStatsIfIndex.description: A pointer to the entry in the ifTable corresponding to this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsRcvLocalFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsRcvLocalFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsRcvLocalFrames.description: Number of frames received where the destination station address is on this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsForwardedFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsForwardedFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsForwardedFrames.description: Number of frames received on this port and forwarded to another port or to the system module for processing.

ciscoTsPortStatsStations.name: ciscoTsPortStatsStations
ciscoTsPortStatsStations.description: Number of active stations in the address table for this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsSWHandledFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsSWHandledFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsSWHandledFrames.description: Number of frames received on this port and delivered to the system module for processing.

ciscoTsPortStatsLocalStations.name: ciscoTsPortStatsLocalStations
ciscoTsPortStatsLocalStations.description: Number of stations on this port which belong to the local segment.

ciscoTsPortStatsRemoteStations.name: ciscoTsPortStatsRemoteStations
ciscoTsPortStatsRemoteStations.description: Number of stations on this port which belong to another segment.

ciscoTsPortStatsUnknownStaFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsUnknownStaFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsUnknownStaFrames.description: Number of unicast frames received on this port and forwarded to the system module for processing because the source or destination station address is not in the port's forwarding table.

ciscoTsPortStatsResetTimer.name: ciscoTsPortStatsResetTimer
ciscoTsPortStatsResetTimer.description: Time (in 100th second ticks) since the port counters were reset.

ciscoTsPortStatsInFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsInFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsInFrames.description: Total number of frames received on this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsOutFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsOutFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsOutFrames.description: Total number of frames transmitted by this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsLongFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsLongFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsLongFrames.description: Total number of frames received on this port which were too long.

ciscoTsPortStatsShortFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsShortFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsShortFrames.description: Total number of frames received on this port which were too short.

ciscoTsPortStatsInBufOverflows.name: ciscoTsPortStatsInBufOverflows
ciscoTsPortStatsInBufOverflows.description: Total number of frames received on this port which caused a receive buffer overflow.

ciscoTsPortStatsOutBufOverflows.name: ciscoTsPortStatsOutBufOverflows
ciscoTsPortStatsOutBufOverflows.description: Total number of frames which could not be transmitted from this port because of transmit buffer overflow.

ciscoTsPortStatsRcvBcasts.name: ciscoTsPortStatsRcvBcasts
ciscoTsPortStatsRcvBcasts.description: Number of broadcast frames received on this port without errors.

ciscoTsPortStatsRcvMcasts.name: ciscoTsPortStatsRcvMcasts
ciscoTsPortStatsRcvMcasts.description: Number of multicast frames received on this port without errors.

ciscoTsPortStatsSwitchedFrames.name: ciscoTsPortStatsSwitchedFrames
ciscoTsPortStatsSwitchedFrames.description: Number of frames switched on this port.

ciscoTsPortStatsPktsInErrors.name: ciscoTsPortStatsPktsInErrors
ciscoTsPortStatsPktsInErrors.description: Total number of packets received or transmitted from this port in which there was an error.

ciscoTsPortStatsAddrChainOverflows.name: ciscoTsPortStatsAddrChainOverflows
ciscoTsPortStatsAddrChainOverflows.description: Number of times an address chain was full when trying to add an entry to the port address table.

ciscoTsPortStatsTableOverflows.name: ciscoTsPortStatsTableOverflows
ciscoTsPortStatsTableOverflows.description: Number of times the address table was full when trying to add an entry to the port address table.

ciscoTsPortStatsCfgLoss.name: ciscoTsPortStatsCfgLoss
ciscoTsPortStatsCfgLoss.description: Number of events, as described in ciscoTsPortCfgLossRC, after the port has completed the join process and then lost communication.

ciscoTsPortStatsCfgLossRC.name: ciscoTsPortStatsCfgLossRC
ciscoTsPortStatsCfgLossRC.description: Reason code describing the cause of the latest configuration loss. A value of no-cfg-loss(7) will be returned when there has not been a configuration loss.

ciscoTsPortStatsTrCRF.name: ciscoTsPortStatsTrCRF
ciscoTsPortStatsTrCRF.description: The TrCRF or TrCRFs that a port is assigned to. Only trunk ports such as ISL and ATM can be members of multiple TrCRFs. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight TrCRFs, with the first octet specifying TrCRFs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying TrCRFs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered TrCRF, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered TrCRF. Thus, each TrCRF of the stack is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then the port is assigned to that TrCRF. If that bit has a value of '0', then the port is not assigned to the TrCRF.

ciscoTsPortStatsAutoDisableRC.name: ciscoTsPortStatsAutoDisableRC
ciscoTsPortStatsAutoDisableRC.description: Reason code describing the cause for a port having been disabled by the switch software. A value of not-disabled(1) will be returned when the port has not been disabled by the switch software.

ciscoTsPassiveProbeTable.name: ciscoTsPassiveProbeTable
ciscoTsPassiveProbeTable.description: Passive probe port configuration table. There are always two entries in the table. These entries cannot be administratively deleted and no rows can be created.

ciscoTsPassiveProbeEntry.name: ciscoTsPassiveProbeEntry
ciscoTsPassiveProbeEntry.description: Definition of each row in the table.

ciscoTsPassiveProbeIndex.name: ciscoTsPassiveProbeIndex
ciscoTsPassiveProbeIndex.description: Index into the Passive Probe port table. The following table describes the configuration options for the ciscoTsPassiveProbeTable. The PortMode column represents the operational mode of the ciscoTsPassiveProbeMonitoredPort. Index PortMode Probe Direction --------------------------------------------- 1 HDX both 1 FDX receive 2 HDX both 2 FDX transmit Set the objects in this table according to how you want to monitor the traffic.

ciscoTsPassiveProbePort.name: ciscoTsPassiveProbePort
ciscoTsPassiveProbePort.description: The port that is configured to mirror traffic from another port in the switch. This is the port to which you can connect an RMON probe. Setting this object to zero turns off the passive probe.

ciscoTsPassiveProbeMonitoredPort.name: ciscoTsPassiveProbeMonitoredPort
ciscoTsPassiveProbeMonitoredPort.description: The port that will have its traffic mirrored onto the probe port. Set this object to a non-zero value to have that port's traffic copied to the monitoring port. The default value is 0.

ciscoTsPassiveProbeDirection.name: ciscoTsPassiveProbeDirection
ciscoTsPassiveProbeDirection.description: Direction of traffic flow that is being monitored.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTable.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTable
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTable.description: TrCRF information table. There is one entry for each TrCRF in a stack. Entries are administratively created and deleted via the vtpEditControlTable.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoEntry.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoEntry
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoEntry.description: Definition of each row in the TrCRF Table

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber.description: Unique identifier for this entry in the TrCRF table. Corresponds to the TrCRF number. It is also the index into the vtpVLANEntry table which is in the VTP MIB.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoName.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoName
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoName.description: User defined name of the TrCRF. The name can only be set in the VTP MIB.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeProtoSpecifi.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeProtoSpecification
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeProtoSpecifi.description: The Spanning Tree Protocol to run on this TrCRF.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeForwar.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeForwardDelay
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeForwar.description: The value used as the Forwarding Delay in this TrCRF. The range for this parameter is 400 to 3000 and is related to the value of dtrSpanningTreeBridgeMaxAge. See 802.1D-1990 for the relationship between dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge and dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay. The granularity of this timer is specified to be 1/100 of a second. This agent will return a 'badValue' error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeHelloT.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeHelloTime
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeHelloT.description: The value to be used as the Hello Time in this TrCRF. The range for this parameter is 100 to 1000. The granularity of this timer is specified to be 1/100 of a second. This agent will return a 'badValue' error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeMaxAge.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeMaxAge
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeBridgeMaxAge.description: The value to be used as the Max Age in this TrCRF. The range for this parameter is 600 to 4000 and is related to the value of dtrSpanningTreeBridgeHelloTime. See 802.1D-1990 for the relationship between dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge and dot1dStpBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified to be 1/100 of a second. This agent will return a 'badValue' error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeInternalPort.name: ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeInternalPortMode
ciscoTsTrCRFInfoSpanningTreeInternalPort.description: Used when configuring manual spanning tree. Setting this object to forwarding(2) or blocking(3) overrides the spanning tree's algorithm for TrCRF's logical internal port that connects it to the TrBRF.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTable.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTable
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTable.description: TrBRF information table. There is one entry for each TrBRF in a stack. Entries are administratively created and deleted via the vtpEditControlTable.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoEntry.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoEntry
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoEntry.description: Definition of each row in the TrBRF Table

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber.description: Unique identifier for this entry in the TrBRF table. Corresponds to the TrBRF number. It is also the index into the vtpVLANEntry table which is in the VTP MIB.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoName.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoName
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoName.description: User defined name of the TrBRF. The name can only be set in the VTP MIB.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpAddress.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpAddress
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpAddress.description: IP Address assigned to this TrBRF. Changes to the IP Address of the TrBRF to which the management station belongs cause loss of connectivity until the management station updates its information about the IP Address.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpSubnetMask.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpSubnetMask
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this TrBRF.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpDefaultGateway.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpDefaultGateway
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIpDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway for this TrBRF.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoStpMode.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoStpMode
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoStpMode.description: This object is used to enable or disable the Spanning Tree Protocol for this TrBRF.

ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIEEEStpUsesBridgeFuncAdd.name: ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIEEEStpUsesBridgeFuncAddr
ciscoTsTrBRFInfoIEEEStpUsesBridgeFuncAdd.description: Enables the IEEE Spanning Tree Protocol at the TrBRF level to use the IBM bridge functional address instead of the default IEEE functional address.

ciscoTsTransitedConfiguredTrCRFs.name: ciscoTsTransitedConfiguredTrCRFs
ciscoTsTransitedConfiguredTrCRFs.description: A string of octets containing one bit per TrCRF in the management domain. The first octet corresponds to TrCRFs with ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber 1 through 8; the second octet to TrCRFs 9 through 16; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber in that octet. If the bit correspond to a TrCRF is set to '1', then the TrCRF is a transited configured TrCRF on the local device. (Default TrCRFs which must transit the local device are always considered to be 'transited configured TrCRFs'.) Any attempt to: set a bit string which has more bits set than the local device can transit; or does not have all bits set corresponding to default TrCRFs which must transit the device; or set any bits corresponding to non-existant TrCRFs (TrCRFs whose IDs are not defined in the management domain) will be rejected with a 'badValue' error.

ciscoTsTransitedTrCRFs.name: ciscoTsTransitedTrCRFs
ciscoTsTransitedTrCRFs.description: A string of octets containing one bit per TrCRF in the management domain. The first octet corresponds to TrCRFs with ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber 1 through 8; the second octet to TrCRFs 9 through 16; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value ciscoTsTrCRFInfoTrCRFNumber in that octet. If the bit corresponding to a TrCRF is set to '1', then the TrCRF transits the local device either because it was configured to or because it was selected to automatically by the selection algorithm.

ciscoTsTransitedConfiguredTrBRFs.name: ciscoTsTransitedConfiguredTrBRFs
ciscoTsTransitedConfiguredTrBRFs.description: A string of octets containing one bit per TrBRF in the management domain. The first octet corresponds to TrBRFs with ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber 1 through 8; the second octet to TrBRFs 9 through 16; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber in that octet. If the bit correspond to a TrBRF is set to '1', then the TrBRF is a transited configured TrBRF on the local device. (Default TrBRFs which must transit the local device are always considered to be 'transited configured TrBRFs'.) Any attempt to: set a bit string which has more bits set than the local device can transit; or does not have all bits set corresponding to default TrBRFs which must transit the device; or set any bits corresponding to non-existant TrBRFs (TrBRFs whose IDs are not defined in the management domain) will be rejected with a 'badValue' error.

ciscoTsTransitedTrBRFs.name: ciscoTsTransitedTrBRFs
ciscoTsTransitedTrBRFs.description: A string of octets containing one bit per TrBRF in the management domain. The first octet corresponds to TrBRFs with ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber 1 through 8; the second octet to TrBRFs 9 through 16; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value ciscoTsTrBRFInfoTrBRFNumber in that octet. If the bit corresponding to a TrBRF is set to '1', then the TrBRF transits the local device either because it was configured to or because it was selected to automatically by the selection algorithm.

ciscoTsTCTable.name: ciscoTsTCTable
ciscoTsTCTable.description: The TokenChannel table. There are always eight entries in the table, one for each possible channel. These entries cannot be administratively deleted and no entries may be created.

ciscoTsTCEntry.name: ciscoTsTCEntry
ciscoTsTCEntry.description: Definition of each row in the TokenChannel table.

ciscoTsTCSwitchNumber.name: ciscoTsTCSwitchNumber
ciscoTsTCSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoTsTCNumber.name: ciscoTsTCNumber
ciscoTsTCNumber.description: The unique identifier for this row. Corresponds to the TokenChannel number.

ciscoTsTCPorts.name: ciscoTsTCPorts
ciscoTsTCPorts.description: The set of ports in this switch which are active in this channel. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of configured ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. Set requests containing '1' values in one or more bit positions which do not have a '1' value in the corresponding position in ciscoTsStackSwitchPorts will fail with a 'badValue' error. The maximum number of ports in a channel and therefore the maximum number of bits in this object containing '1' values is 8.

ciscoTsTCStatus.name: ciscoTsTCStatus
ciscoTsTCStatus.description: The current running status of the channel.

ciscoTsTCActivePorts.name: ciscoTsTCActivePorts
ciscoTsTCActivePorts.description: The set of ports in this switch which are active in this channel. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of active ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. The maximum number of ports in a channel and therefore the maximum number of bits in this object containing '1' values is 8.

ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterTable.name: ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterTable
ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterTable.description: DSAP and SNAP Filter Class table. This table is global for the entire stack.

ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterEntry.name: ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterEntry
ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter class table. There are 15 entries in the table, one for each protocol class. These entries cannot be administratively deleted and no entries may be created.

ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterEtype.name: ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterEtype
ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterEtype.description: This is the two byte ether-type for this protocol class. Only one ether type may be set per protocol class. Setting an illegal ether type will result in a 'badValue' error. Only 8 ether types can be configured. This object is only configurable for the first 8 protocol class objects.

ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterDSAPs.name: ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterDSAPs
ciscoTsProtocolClassFilterDSAPs.description: This is the list of DSAPs associated with a protocol class. Up to sixteen DSAPs may be specified per protocol class. If any DSAP is an illegal value the entire object will be rejected.

ciscoTsProtocolFilterTable.name: ciscoTsProtocolFilterTable
ciscoTsProtocolFilterTable.description: DSAP and SNAP Filter table. This table allows you to assign protocol classes and settings for each port. There is one entry in the table for each protocol class which has been enabled for filtering.

ciscoTsProtocolFilterEntry.name: ciscoTsProtocolFilterEntry
ciscoTsProtocolFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter table.

ciscoTsProtocolFilterPort.name: ciscoTsProtocolFilterPort
ciscoTsProtocolFilterPort.description: This is the port in the switch to which this table entry corresponds.

ciscoTsProtocolFilterBlockingMode.name: ciscoTsProtocolFilterBlockingMode
ciscoTsProtocolFilterBlockingMode.description: This determines the frame types that will be blocked for this protocol class on this port. Setting the values causes the following: all(1) - causes all frames in this class to be blocked sr(2) - causes source route frames in this class to be blocked nsr(3) - causes non source routed frames in this class to be blocked none(4) - allow all frames in this protocol class. This is the default value.

ciscoTsProtocolFilterTranspMode.name: ciscoTsProtocolFilterTranspMode
ciscoTsProtocolFilterTranspMode.description: If this port is in a SRT configured TrCRF, then setting this object will allow transparent bridging of frames in this protocol class. Setting this object to disable disallows transparent bridging of frames in this protocol class. The default value is enable.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterTable.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterTable
ciscoTsMACDestFilterTable.description: A table of destination filters set up in the switch. New filters are created by adding entries to this table. Note that values for all of the relevant objects for a particular type of filter must be specified in a single SNMP set operation on creation of a filter. Set operations which do not contain all of the required objects for a given filter type will fail with an error-status of 'genErr'. The objects required for each filter type are as follows: ciscoTsMACDestFilterType | Required Objects for Creation ======================== | ============================= block-dest(1) | ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts ---------------------------|-------------------------------- allow-dest(2) | ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts ---------------------------|-------------------------------- limited-multicast(3) | ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts | ciscoTsMACDestFilterExitMask ---------------------------|-------------------------------- force-dest(4) | ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts | ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemoteBox | ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemotePort Since the indices for the table are switch number, MAC address, and filter type, the instance information for a given object specifies which filter is being created. For example, a set request for ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts.s.a1.a2.a3.a4.a5.a6.t will create a filter of type 't' (as enumerated for ciscoTsMACDestFilterType) for MAC address a1:a2:a3:a4:a5:a6 on switch number 's'.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterEntry.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterEntry
ciscoTsMACDestFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter table.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterSwitchNumber.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterSwitchNumber
ciscoTsMACDestFilterSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterStationAddress.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterStationAddress
ciscoTsMACDestFilterStationAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterType.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterType
ciscoTsMACDestFilterType.description: There are three types of destination MAC address filters: (1) Block destination address at specific ports. Indicates that the specified ports must not send frames to the specified destination station address. (2) Allow destination address at specific ports. Indicates that the specified ports must send frames to the specified destination stations only. (3) Force destination address to specific ports. This may be used for two purposes: a. Allow forwarding to a unicast address, which has not been learned. b. Limit forwarding of a multicast address to certain ports. Note, that this filter will only be applied to NSR frames. (4) Limited Multicast of address on filtered port(s) to specified exit mask of ports.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts
ciscoTsMACDestFilterPorts.description: The set of ports to which this filter is applied. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterExitMask.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterExitMask
ciscoTsMACDestFilterExitMask.description: The set of output ports to which a limited multicast filter is applied. This object only has a value for Limited Multicast filters. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemoteBox.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemoteBox
ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemoteBox.description: The remote switch to be used for a force destination filter.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemotePort.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemotePort
ciscoTsMACDestFilterRemotePort.description: The remote port to be used for a force destination filter.

ciscoTsMACDestFilterStatus.name: ciscoTsMACDestFilterStatus
ciscoTsMACDestFilterStatus.description: A get request always returns valid(1). Set this object to invalid(2) to delete an entry.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterTable.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterTable
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterTable.description: A table of source filters set up in the switch. New filters are created by adding entries to this table. Note that values for all of the relevant objects for a particular type of filter must be specified in a single SNMP set operation on creation of a filter. Set operations which do not contain all of the required objects for a given filter type will fail with an error-status of 'genErr'. The objects required for each filter type are as follows: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterType | Required Objects for Creation ========================== | ============================= block-src(1) | ciscoTsMACSourceFilterPorts ----------------------------|------------------------------- allow-src(2) | ciscoTsMACSourceFilterPorts Since the indices for the table are switch number, MAC address, and filter type, the instance information for a given object specifies which filter is being created. For example, a set request for ciscoTsMACSourceFilterPorts.s.a1.a2.a3.a4.a5.a6.t will create a filter of type 't' (as enumerated for ciscoTsMACSourceFilterType) for MAC address a1:a2:a3:a4:a5:a6 on switch number 's'.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterEntry.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterEntry
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter table.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterSwitchNumber.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterSwitchNumber
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterStationAddress.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterStationAddress
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterStationAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterType.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterType
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterType.description: There are two types of source address filters: (1) Block source address at specific ports. Indicates that the specific source addresses must not send frames from specified ports. (2) Allow source address at specific ports. Indicates that only the specified source addresses must send frames from the specified ports.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterPorts.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterPorts
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterPorts.description: The set of ports to which this filter is applied. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoTsMACSourceFilterStatus.name: ciscoTsMACSourceFilterStatus
ciscoTsMACSourceFilterStatus.description: A get request always returns valid(1). Set this object to invalid(2) to delete an entry.

ciscoTsDupAddrFilterTable.name: ciscoTsDupAddrFilterTable
ciscoTsDupAddrFilterTable.description: A table of MAC addresses that have been identified as duplicates within an address scope. There is one entry in the tale for each such address. Entries cannot be administratively created/deleted.

ciscoTsDupAddrFilterEntry.name: ciscoTsDupAddrFilterEntry
ciscoTsDupAddrFilterEntry.description: Definition of rows in the duplicate address table.

ciscoTsDupAddrFilterSwitchNumber.name: ciscoTsDupAddrFilterSwitchNumber
ciscoTsDupAddrFilterSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoTsDupAddrFilterStationAddress.name: ciscoTsDupAddrFilterStationAddress
ciscoTsDupAddrFilterStationAddress.description: The MAC address that has been identified as being a duplicate. All frames having this MAC address as their source address are being discarded at the ports specified in ciscoTsDupAddrFilterPorts.

ciscoTsDupAddrFilterPorts.name: ciscoTsDupAddrFilterPorts
ciscoTsDupAddrFilterPorts.description: A bit mask representing all the ports on which this duplicate MAC address is currently being filtered. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports in this switch; the port is not included in this switch if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterTable.name: ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterTable
ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterTable.description: DSAP and SNAP Filter table for trunk ports which support protocol filters on a per-TrCRF basis. This table allows you to assign protocol classes and settings for each TrCRF on each trunk port. There is one entry in the table for each (switch, port, TrCRF, protocol class) tuple for which filtering has been enabled.

ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterEntry.name: ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterEntry
ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter table.

ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterPort.name: ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterPort
ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterPort.description: This is the port in the switch to which this table entry corresponds.

ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterBlockingMode.name: ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterBlockingMode
ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterBlockingMode.description: This determines the frame types that will be blocked for this protocol class on this TrCRF on this port. Setting the values causes the following: all(1) - causes all frames in this class to be blocked sr(2) - causes source route frames in this class to be blocked nsr(3) - causes non source routed frames in this class to be blocked none(4) - allow all frames in this protocol class. This is the default value.

ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterTranspMode.name: ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterTranspMode
ciscoTsTrunkProtocolFilterTranspMode.description: If this port is in a SRT configured TrCRF, then setting this object will allow transparent bridging of frames in this protocol class. Setting this object to disable disallows transparent bridging of frames in this protocol class. The default value is enable.

ciscoTsStackCfgChange.name: ciscoTsStackCfgChange
ciscoTsStackCfgChange.description: This trap is generated when there is a change in the stack configuration i.e. when either a new switch is added to the stack or a switch leaves a stack. ciscoTsNumSwitches indicates the current number of switches which are part of the stack. The management station should update its stack information according to the stack table.

ciscoTsStackProStackMatrixChange.name: ciscoTsStackProStackMatrixChange
ciscoTsStackProStackMatrixChange.description: This trap is generated when the stack switches over from primary to secondary Matrix or from secondary back to primary Matrix.

ciscoTsStackTempChange.name: ciscoTsStackTempChange
ciscoTsStackTempChange.description: This trap is generated when the temperature in a switch exceeds normal or returns to normal.

ciscoTsStackPwrStatusChange.name: ciscoTsStackPwrStatusChange
ciscoTsStackPwrStatusChange.description: This trap is generated when the status of the power supply changes.

ciscoTsPortStrNFwdEntry.name: ciscoTsPortStrNFwdEntry
ciscoTsPortStrNFwdEntry.description: This trap is generated when a port automatically enters store and forward mode when the error rate exceeds the threshold.

ciscoTsPortCfgLossTrap.name: ciscoTsPortCfgLossTrap
ciscoTsPortCfgLossTrap.description: This trap occurs when a port is disabled because it has exceeded its Configuration Loss Threshold within the configured Sampling Period.

ciscoTsBeaconStart.name: ciscoTsBeaconStart
ciscoTsBeaconStart.description: This trap is generated when a port or a station local to a port begins to beacon. It is sent out only when a ring status change indicates that a station is beaconing.

ciscoTsBeaconEnd.name: ciscoTsBeaconEnd
ciscoTsBeaconEnd.description: This trap is generated when the ring status change indicates that a ring is no longer beaconing. This trap only occurs only once when the status actually changes.

ciscoTsDuplicateMACAddr.name: ciscoTsDuplicateMACAddr
ciscoTsDuplicateMACAddr.description: This trap is generated when a duplicate MAC address is detected on a port in a TrCRF which already has learned that MAC address.

ciscoTsPortSoftErrExceededTrap.name: ciscoTsPortSoftErrExceededTrap
ciscoTsPortSoftErrExceededTrap.description: This trap is generated when a station local to a port exceeds its Soft Error Threshold within the configured interval.

ciscoTsTrCRFNewRoot.name: ciscoTsTrCRFNewRoot
ciscoTsTrCRFNewRoot.description: This trap is a TrCRF specific version of the newRoot trap as described in RFC1493. The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election. Implementation of this trap is optional.

ciscoTsTrCRFTopologyChange.name: ciscoTsTrCRFTopologyChange
ciscoTsTrCRFTopologyChange.description: This trap is a TrCRF specific version of the topologyChange trap as described in RFC1493. A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition. Implementation of this trap is optional.

ciscoTsTrBRFNewRoot.name: ciscoTsTrBRFNewRoot
ciscoTsTrBRFNewRoot.description: This trap is a TrBRF specific version of the newRoot trap as described in RFC1493. The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election. Implementation of this trap is optional.

ciscoTsTrBRFTopologyChange.name: ciscoTsTrBRFTopologyChange
ciscoTsTrBRFTopologyChange.description: This trap is a TrBRF specific version of the topologyChange trap as described in RFC1493. A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition. Implementation of this trap is optional.

ciscoTsTokenChannelFailed.name: ciscoTsTokenChannelFailed
ciscoTsTokenChannelFailed.description: This trap is sent when one of the links in an TokenChannel fail. The variable ciscoTsTCPorts contains the ports which are operational in the TokenChannel.

ciscoTsTokenChannelStatus.name: ciscoTsTokenChannelStatus
ciscoTsTokenChannelStatus.description: This trap is sent to report a TokenChannel or ISLChannel status change. The variable ciscoTsTCStatus contains the current channel status. The variable ciscoTsTCPorts contains the ports which are configured in the channel. The variable ciscoTsTCActivePorts contains the ports which are active in the channel.
